properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 25 at 3:00PM MST until January 26 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 MPH with occasional gusts of 60 MPH
possible.

* WHERE...South Laramie Range Foothills including the towns of
Federal...Horse Creek and Whitaker.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM MST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Potential blow off and
blow over risk for light weight and high profile vehicles such
as empty or light load semis and camper trailers.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST SUNDAY
